Source: linux-hello
Section: system
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Linux Hello Team <dev@linuxhello.local>
Build-Depends: 
  debhelper-compat (= 13),
  rustc (>= 1.70),
  cargo,
  libdbus-1-dev,
  libpam0g-dev
Standards-Version: 4.6.1
Homepage: https://github.com/linuxhello/face-auth
Vcs-Git: https://github.com/linuxhello/face-auth.git
Rules-Requires-Root: no

Package: linux-hello
Architecture: any
Depends: 
  ${shlibs:Depends},
  ${misc:Depends},
  dbus,
  systemd
Conflicts: linux-hello-gui
Description: Face Authentication System for Linux
 Linux Hello provides facial recognition authentication for:
 .
  * sudo authentication
  * screenlock unlock (KDE/GNOME)
  * login screen (future)
 .
 This package includes the daemon and PAM module.

Package: linux-hello-daemon
Architecture: any
Depends:
  ${shlibs:Depends},
  ${misc:Depends},
  dbus
Description: Face Authentication Daemon
 The D-Bus service daemon for Linux Hello facial recognition.
 Provides the com.linuxhello.FaceAuth interface.

Package: libpam-linux-hello
Architecture: any
Depends:
  ${shlibs:Depends},
  ${misc:Depends},
  linux-hello-daemon,
  libpam-runtime
Description: PAM module for Linux Hello
 This PAM module integrates Linux Hello facial recognition
 with system authentication (sudo, screenlock, etc).

Package: linux-hello-tools
Architecture: any
Depends:
  ${shlibs:Depends},
  ${misc:Depends}
Description: Command-line tools for Linux Hello
 Includes the linux-hello CLI for managing faces and testing.
